            "content": "# JARVIS Second Brain — Skills & Schema Implementation Plan\n\n> **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Define the JARVIS vault schema in types.yaml and write three skills (second-brain-protocol, jarvis, update using-cortx-cli) that enable AI agents to manage a PARA+GTD Second Brain through cortx.\n\n**Architecture:** Schema-first — types.yaml defines vault structure, second-brain-protocol teaches domain knowledge to all agents, jarvis adds orchestration logic on top. cortx bidirectional relation support is being built in parallel and will unlock `array[link:X]` and `boolean` field types.\n\n**Tech Stack:** cortx CLI, YAML (types.yaml), Markdown (SKILL.md format)\n\n**Scope boundary:** Skills + schema only. cortx engine changes (bidirectional relations, new field types) are tracked separately and being built in parallel.\n\n---\n\n## File Map\n\n**Modified:**\n- `types.yaml` — add `goal`, `log` entities; update `area`, `task`, `note`, `resource` schemas\n- `~/.claude/skills/using-cortx-cli/SKILL.md` — add goal/log entities, new query recipes\n\n**Created:**\n- `~/.claude/skills/second-brain-protocol/SKILL.md` — PARA+GTD domain knowledge for all agents\n- `~/.claude/skills/jarvis/SKILL.md` — JARVIS personal assistant orchestration\n\n---\n\n### Task 1: Update types.yaml with new schema\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `types.yaml`\n\n> **Note:** `boolean`, `number`, and `array[link: X]` field types require cortx engine support being built in parallel. Use `type: string` as a temporary stand-in until cortx supports them. Intent is documented via inline comments.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Replace types.yaml with new schema**\n\n```yaml\ntypes:\n  area:\n    folder: \"2_Areas\"\n    required: [id, type, title]\n    fields:\n      id:         { type: string }\n      type